				<h1 class="main-heading">Privacy</h1>
				<h3>INTRODUCTION</h3>
				<p>Anchor ID, Inc. is focused on maintaining your privacy. With respect to your personal data, Anchor ID provides an important service to our customers to help, which makes it easier to use the web and mobile apps without the need to share personal data, and we start with this privacy policy. In short, we simply don't collect personal data about our customers, making it impossible for us to share it. That's right &ndash; we don't know, and don't ask you to tell us, your name, your address, your home or work phone number, your age, your gender, etc. We don't even require your email address if your don't want to share it.</p>
				<p>To operate our service, however, we only need the following three items:</p>
				<p>Mobile Phone Number: We ask for your mobile phone number, but only to verify that you can receive an activation code via text message, and to verify that you know the correct billing zip code for this account. Otherwise, we will never, ever, sell or share your mobile phone number with anyone.</p>
				<p>Voice Sample: We ask for your voice sample during registrations to ensure that you have a backup to your PIN. If you forget your PIN, your voice sample becomes our only way to recover your account. You also have the option of using this voice sample to log in to your accounts. Otherwise, we will never, ever, sell or share your Voice Sample with anyone.</p>
				<p>Zip Code: We ask for your zip code, and we may verify that you have entered the correct zip code with your mobile network operator. We may aggregate information about you with others in your zip code, and share with third parties.</p>
				<p>We want you to use Anchor ID to access many web sites and mobile apps. But, we also want you to trust us, which is why we will never ask for this personal data.</p>
				<p>Use of all information collected is detailed </p>

				<h3>APPLICABILITY OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY</h3>
				<p>This Privacy Policy describes Anchor ID, Inc.'s (&quot;Anchor ID&quot; or &quot;we&quot;) practices for gathering, storing, using and sharing information collected or otherwise obtained by Anchor ID both (i) via this website (the &quot;Website&quot;) and (ii) through your download (via a mobile device, tablet or other computer) of Anchor ID software or mobile apps (collectively, &quot;Applicable Software&quot;) and/or use of Anchor ID services facilitated by such Applicable Software (the &quot;Services&quot;), regardless of whether the Applicable Software or Services are branded as &quot;Anchor ID&quot; or as any Applicable Third Party (defined below). This Privacy Policy does not apply to any information that may be collected by Anchor ID through any other means, including offline. By visiting the Website or downloading and/or using the Applicable Software or the Services you are providing your explicit permission to Anchor ID to collect, store, use and share information as set forth in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms and conditions set forth in this Privacy Policy, please do not use, download or access the Website or any Applicable Software, or the Services. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary herein, this Privacy Policy does not apply to information about you collected (i) by third party services, applications or websites, or advertisements associated with, linked to or otherwise accessible from the Website (including by a third party payment processor) or (ii) by third party individuals, retailers, financial institutions or other firms or companies, including your employer or client (collectively, &quot;Applicable Third Parties&quot;), with which you conduct transactions or communications facilitated and/or confirmed through use of the Services (&quot;Third Party Transactions&quot;).The information collected or received by such third parties is subject to their own privacy policies and under no circumstances is Anchor ID responsible or liable for the third party's compliance therewith.</p>

				<h3>HOW WE COLLECT INFORMATION</h3>
				<p>You can visit the Website anonymously without telling us who you are and without giving or having us collect any personal information about yourself. We collect limited personally identifiable information (i) when you register to become a user of the Services through the Website or in connection with the download the Applicable Software, (ii) when you sign up for an Anchor ID online service demonstration, (iii) when you &quot;opt in&quot; for certain services or features of the Website, such as electing to receive emails, (iv) when you voluntarily provide us with information through emails, and (iv) automatically as further described below. We receive the automatic and passive data (both personally identifiable and otherwise) from the computer, mobile phone or other device you use to download the Applicable Software or access and use the Website or the Services. In this regard, the Website uses common automated information gathering tools such as log files and &quot;cookies&quot; that identify users and record page activity, including a particular user's visits to a page and how many &quot;hits&quot; a particular item is receiving, as well as other user activity and interactions with the Website. Third party advertisements or functionality, which may be included on the Website, may also contain cookies sent by Internet advertising companies, advertisers or others (known as &quot;third party cookies&quot;). Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but it is possible to change your browser setup so that it warns you each time a cookie is being sent, blocks third party cookies or blocks or rejects all cookies. However, rejecting cookies may prevent you from taking advantage of certain portions of the Website.</p>

				<h3>WHAT INFORMATION WE COLLECT</h3>
				<p>Via the Website. Via the Website, Anchor ID collects from you: (i) certain non-personal technical and other information and (ii) certain personally identifiable information. Non-Registered Users of the Website &ndash; In general, if you use the Website without registering with Anchor ID, you will be using the Website anonymously; no personally identifiable information is collected. However, we will collect certain non-personally identifiable information from non-registered users, as noted in &quot;All Users&quot; paragraph below. Registered Users of the Website &ndash; When you register with the Website, including registering for a demonstration, you will be asked to provide us with certain personally identifiable information, which may include a nickname (we do not require your legal name), zip code, voice sample and mobile phone numbers; email address; other contact information; and your 'Anchor ID Universal User Name'. Providing some of the requested information may be optional and Anchor ID will indicate what information is required and what is optional.</p>
				<p>All Users &ndash; Regardless of whether you are a registered or non-registered user, when you use the Website various types of information are collected automatically and passively through log files, cookies and the other common tools. This information may include your IP address (a number assigned to your computer when you use the Internet), the name of the web page from which you entered the Website, the type of browser or operating system you are using, the name of your Internet service provider, broad demographic data, your activity while using the Website (including access times, duration of visit on each page, new and repeat visit information, exit page information and general usage activity), and data relating to malfunctions or problems occurring when you use your computer with the Website.</p>
				<p>Discretionary Contact With Us &ndash; The Website provides information on how to contact us electronically through the Website and through email. Whenever you make such contact, you will be providing us with your name and contact information, such as email address, and any information you choose to include in the text of your message.</p>
				<p>Tracking &ndash; From the Website, we do not engage in the collection of personally identifiable information about your online activities over time and across third party websites or online services. Accordingly, we do not currently process or comply with any web browser's &quot;do not track&quot; signal or other mechanisms that provide consumers with the ability to exercise choice regarding the collection of personally identifiable information about your online activities over time and across third party websites. From time to time, we may allow third-party companies which provide advertisements or certain functionality to collect certain anonymous information when you visit our website. These companies may collect and use such information during your visits to this and other websites in order to provide advertisements on other sites about goods and services likely to be of greater interest to you. These companies will typically use a cookie or a third party web beacon to collect this information.</p>
				<p>Via the Applicable Software and the Services. When you download the Applicable Software and use the Services, you will provide to Anchor ID, and its affiliates will otherwise collect, types of personally identifiable information, including types not usually obtained through typical website usage or web-based applications. This information is used to identify and protect your accounts and communications, and includes technical, usage and other data and information, such as contact information (e.g. phone and email), authentication credentials (e.g. passwords, biometric information), location and GPS information, device information (such as device OS version and device hardware), unique device identifiers (including device IP address and mobile serial number), application software and peripherals. In addition, Anchor ID will collect data and information about your Third Party Transactions, including login times and usage activities log (collectively, &quot;Transaction Data&quot;); provided, however, that Anchor ID will not collect the content of transactions or communications between you and Applicable Third Parties that may be delivered through the your use of the Services.</p>
				<p>Tracking &ndash;Via the Applicable Software and the Services, we do not engage in the collection of personally identifiable information about your online activities across third party websites or online services. However, we do collect information (including Transaction Data) from your use of the Applicable Software and the Services across different Applicable Third Parties with whom you conduct Third Party Transaction.</p>

