				<h3>COMMUNICATION YOU MAY RECEIVE FROM US/OPT-OUT</h3>
				<p>Anchor ID uses voluntarily provided information to send you announcements of new services, updates, promotional information and newsletters, as well as to provide the Services that you request and give you better customer service. You may opt out of receiving promotional materials or other communications from us by checking the appropriate box when you register. You may unsubscribe or &quot;opt out&quot; from these emails at any time by following the opt-out link provided in any email you received from us or by contacting us via the email address at the end of this Privacy Policy. Please note that even if you unsubscribe from promotional email messages, we may still contact you. For example, even if you have unsubscribed from our email messages, we will still send you emails confirming your preferences. Further, so long as you are using the Services, we will need to contact you with important information related to your Services account, including activation and deactivation notices, transactional information, and notices from Applicable Third Parties.</p>

				<h3>SECURITY</h3>
				<p>Anchor ID stores personally identifiable information in a secure manner and considers it to be part of the assets of its business. To prevent unauthorized access, maintain data accuracy and ensure the appropriate use of information, Anchor ID has put in place physical, electronic and administrative procedures to safeguard and secure the information it collects online. However, the Internet and data security are constantly evolving. As such, you should consider any communication or information you transmit to Anchor ID through unsecured means as non&ndash;confidential. You agree that Anchor ID will not be liable or responsible if information that belongs to you is intercepted and used by an unauthorized recipient.</p>

				<h3>MODIFICATIONS AND DELETIONS TO PERSONAL INFORMATION</h3>
				<p>We strive to maintain the accuracy of any personally identifiable information that may be collected from you, and will use our commercially reasonable efforts to respond promptly to update our database when you tell us the information in our database is not accurate. The mobile app provides you with access to your account profile and the ability to edit this information at the Account Management tab. Once you are no longer a registered Website user and cease to use the Applicable Software and Services, your account may be permanently deleted from the Anchor ID servers. Any such removed information may persist in backup copies for a reasonable period of time but will not be generally available. Certain information is needed to provide you with the Services, so we may delete this information only after you delete your account. Some of the things you do through the Services or on the Website are not stored in your account, but with business firms contracted to provide specific services to us, such as a credit card processing company or SMS providers. Such information may only be deleted in accordance with the privacy policy of such third parties. See above under the caption &quot;Our Sharing of Information&quot; in the section &quot;How Is Your Information Used?&quot;</p>

